sentences.english: Camden ranked second this year, with Detroit, Michigan;
sentences.chinese: 根据这份报告，今年卡姆登市位居第二。

sentences.english: Bihar’s public services and infrastructure are among the worst in India.
sentences.chinese: 比哈尔邦的公共服务和基础设施位居印度最差行列。

sentences.english: According to The Tribune, Gunnell topped the list for the third straight year.
sentences.chinese: 根据这份名单，古纳尔已是第三年位居名单首位了。

sentences.english: Madonna has the number one song on the pop music charts.
sentences.chinese: 麦当那的歌曲在流行歌曲排行榜上位居第一。

sentences.english: While Brad Pitt who act in Inglourious Basterds ranks at third.
sentences.chinese: 出演《无耻混蛋》的布拉德皮特位居第三。

sentences.english: Former Central Bank Governor Ahmed Ould Daddah was third with less than 14 percent.
sentences.chinese: 前中央银行行长达达赫得票不到14%，位居第三。

sentences.english: Xiao gang ranks first among the contestants who already got their results.
sentences.chinese: 已知成绩的参赛选手中，小刚位居第一。

sentences.english: Second-placed Citic Securities Co. posted 7.3 billion yuan in profit.
sentences.chinese: 位居第二的中信证券公司公布盈利为73亿元人民币。

sentences.english: We had the third largest market share in the PRC property and casualty insurance market in 2002.
sentences.chinese: 年本公司位居中国财产保险市场占有率第三。

sentences.english: Holidays length of the sections in the Tang Dynasty, the first place.
sentences.chinese: 假期之长，在唐朝各节中位居第一。

sentences.english: The second most common"profession"is that of businessman.
sentences.chinese: 位居政坛中最普遍“职业”次席的是商人。

sentences.english: Haikou, Yueyang, ranked second and third places.
sentences.chinese: 海口，岳阳则分别位居第二，第三位。

sentences.english: Lonmin is the world's third largest platinum producer.
sentences.chinese: 隆明公司的铂金出产量位居世界第三。

sentences.english: South Korea's Seoul ranked third, followed closely by Tokyo at No. 4.
sentences.chinese: 韩国的首尔名列第三，东京紧跟其后，位居第四。

sentences.english: It enters our darkest records countdown at Number 44.
sentences.chinese: 在我们的最黑暗唱片排行榜中位居44名。

sentences.english: India is first, however, in the production of mangoes and bananas.
sentences.chinese: 但印度的芒果和香蕉产量位居第一。
